      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here is the `smith_waterman` function that calculates the local alignment score using dynamic programming for your DNA sequences. They printf the maximum score found in the matrix to confirm the final result:\n\n```python\ndef smith_waterman(seq1, seq2, match=2, mismatch=-1, gap=-1):\n    rows = len(seq2) + 1\n    cols = len(seq1) + 1\n    matrix = [[0] * cols for _ in range(rows)]\n\n    for i in range(1, rows):\n        for j in range(1, cols):\n            score = mismatch if seq1[j-1] != seq2[i-1] else match\n            matrix[i][j] = max(0, matrix[i-1][j-1] + score, matrix[i-1][j] + gap, matrix[i][j-1] + gap)\n            \n    return max(max(row) for row in matrix)\n```",
